article.description: — Lydell Elmore and John-Michael Wright each scored 14 points as High Point easily beat William & Mary 71-49 on Saturday.
article.headline: Elmore, Wright lead High Point past William & Mary 71-49
article.linkText: Elmore, Wright lead High Point past William & Mary 71-49
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- — Lydell Elmore and John-Michael Wright each scored 14 points as High Point easily beat William & Mary 71-49 on Saturday. Bryson Childress chipped in 12 points and Ahmil Flowers had 10 points and seven rebounds for High Point (2-4). Luke Loewe had 13 points for the Tribe (2-2). Yuri Covington added 10 points. Quinn Blair had 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
